    <!-- 2. Google My Business -->
    <article class="section-card">
      <h2><span class="icon">📍</span>Google My Business: The Foundation of Local SEO India</h2>
      <p><strong>Local SEO India</strong> starts with one free tool that most businesses set up wrong or ignore entirely: Google My Business (GMB). When someone searches "CA near me in Surat" or "best fabric shop Surat," GMB is what shows up first — even before websites.</p>
      <h3>How to Set Up GMB the Right Way</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Claim your listing</strong> at business.google.com with your exact business name</li>
        <li><strong>Add every detail:</strong> address, phone, website, hours, category</li>
        <li><strong>Upload 15–20 real photos</strong> of your shop, products, and team</li>
        <li><strong>Collect reviews</strong> — ask every happy customer to leave one on Google</li>
        <li><strong>Post weekly</strong> — Google lets you share offers, events, and updates</li>
        <li><strong>Answer Q&A</strong> — even write questions yourself and answer them</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Why Reviews Matter for Local SEO India</h3>
      <p>Google prioritizes businesses with more recent, positive reviews. A shop with 80 five-star reviews will outrank a competitor with 10. Create a simple WhatsApp message that says: <em>"Thank you for visiting! Could you spare 30 seconds to leave us a review? [Google link]"</em></p>
      <div class="highlight-box">
        📌 <strong>Surat Tip:</strong> Use keywords in your GMB description like "digital marketing agency in Surat" or "saree shop in Varachha Surat." Local keyword placement directly boosts your visibility in nearby searches.
      </div>
    </article>

